OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Ken Hay
OL,5,F"He was a corporal, he didn't have to
OL,6,Fcome.
OL,8,F"He volunteered to take a chap's place
OL,9,Fwho was married with children,
OL,10,Factually he got back but got badly
OL,11,Fwounded on Hill 112 a couple of days
OL,12,Flater. I didn't know until later.
OL,14,F"Of our patrol of 30, I found out
OL,15,Fafter the war, 26 got back. The battle
OL,16,Flasted two or three hours. Five of us
OL,17,Fgot captured and nine were killed.
OL,19,F"You have got bullets coming at you.
