OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Ken Hay
OL,5,F"I think they were watching what we
OL,6,Fwere doing. We didn't know. And so
OL,7,Fwhen we made ourselves comfortable
OL,8,Fthey just stepped out with guns
OL,9,Ftrained on us and that was that bit of
OL,10,Fthe war finished for me."
OL,12,FMr Hay was taken to Poland to work in
OL,13,Fa coal mine.
OL,15,FAs the Allies advanced he and other
OL,16,Fprisoners were forced to march
OL,17,Fhundreds of miles before being
OL,18,Fabandoned by their guards.
